    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m selling my absolute pride and joy. This car is in incredible, showroom-quality shape\u2014honestly, it looks and drives like it just rolled off the lot! I\u2019ve babied this thing since day one, keeping it spotless and always garaged. If you\u2019re looking for a ride that\u2019s basically perfect and ready for a new home, this is the one. You've gotta see it in person to believe how clean it is!",
      "price": 43900.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is an exceptional 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in concours-ready condition. This S54-powered icon features the 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, boasting individual throttle bodies and a high-revving 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a factory-spec variable M differential lock. Mechanically flawless, the vehicle has undergone proactive rod bearing replacement and comprehensive rear subframe reinforcement. The chassis retains its factory-fresh rigidity with original Sachs dampers and bushings. This is a collector-grade example with documented service history, flawless paint depth, and zero deferred maintenance.",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Mint condition. Single owner. Full service history. No cosmetic or mechanical defects. Garage kept. New tires.",
      "price": 44500.0,
